The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Dance for a cause

 Tata and Astad Deboo Dance Foundation present Contraposition, a choreographic performance by Astad Deboo, along with dancers from the Clarke School for the Deaf, Chennai. The result of more than three years? training with a group of physically challenged yet immensely talented students, Deboo?s latest composition has travelled across the seas, with shows being held in Australia, Malaysia and Singapore. Based on the navarasas, or the nine emotions of the natyashastra, this evening?s performance will raise funds for Prerak, a support group for cancer patients. Cards available at Kookie Jar (Rawdon Street and Alipore) and Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre and Seagull Bookstore (Bhowanipore). Apart from this, there will also be a performance of the same presentation this morning at 10.30 at G.D. Birla Sabhagar only for students of special schools in the city.

 Event: Dance performance by Astad Deboo and dancers of the Clarke School for the Deaf, Chennai

 When: Today at 6 pm

 Where: G.D. Birla Sabhagar




